        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 12:03AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1203 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Loma Alta, or 15 miles southeast of Tilden, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Clegg.

This includes US Highway 59 between mile markers 726 and 744.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
